  "texts": [
    "It aids in shaping the application's design, meeting the organization's security objectives, and minimizing risk [150].",
    "In the planning step of DevSecOps, threat modeling proactively identifies security concerns and integrates security measures into the development process from the outset.",
    "One widely adopted framework for threat modeling is STRIDE proposed by Howard and Lipner [88], which categorizes threats into six main types: Spoofing, Tampering, Repudiation, Information Disclosure, Denial of Service (DoS), and Elevation of Privilege.",
    "On the other hand, the DREAD framework proposed by [112] provides a structured approach to assess the severity of identified threats.",
    "DREAD stands for Damage potential, Reproducibility, Exploitability, Affected users, and Discoverability."
  ],
